for you. I think you will swing back to our West, but New York is your college now, and to think, Enot, you are paying your own way in the big school! You must set aside a certain reasonable amount to be spent for seeing good plays. You should hear some opera see art galleries. Try not to miss the more important things in New York. 
You have not yet met Dave's, & how fine that will be & how different it will make you feel, and you haven't yet met any of the people, I know, when I get home I'll write letters to some people for you. Lackam is in England or you would have seen him by now. 
I feel what you feel so deeply I love you, dear. 
Your Dad 